# Normalize line endings to LF in the repository AND in the working tree.
#
# Without this, core.autocrlf=true on Windows checks every file out as CRLF,
# and `composer phpcs` fails on all of them with
# Generic.Files.LineEndings.InvalidEOLChar before it ever looks at the code —
# so the mandatory local QA gate is unrunnable on Windows while CI (Linux, LF)
# stays green. `eol=lf` pins the checkout, not just the blob.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Serena (MCP code-navigation server) rewrites its own config with NATIVE line
# endings by design — on Windows that means CRLF. Against the `eol=lf` rule
# above that produces a file git checks out as LF and Serena immediately
# rewrites as CRLF: permanently dirty, and noise in every `git status`.
# `-text` opts these out of normalisation entirely, so git stores whatever
# bytes Serena wrote and stops arguing with it. Nothing here is linted, so the
# reason `eol=lf` exists in the first place (PHPCS on Windows) does not apply.
.serena/** -text

# Binary: never touch these.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.ico binary
*.mo binary
